               <p>THOMAS GRIFFITHS. I am a <rs id="t18320906-276-viclabel1552" type="occupation">
                     <rs id="t18320906-276-deflabel1553" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-276-defend2281 t18320906-276-deflabel1553"></join>
                  </rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-276-victim2283 t18320906-276-viclabel1552"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18320906-276-crimeloc1554">Whitmore-road, Hoxton</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-276-crimeloc1554" type="placeName" value="Whitmore-road, Hoxton"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-276-crimeloc1554" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-276-off1550 t18320906-276-crimeloc1554"></join>. The prisoner is my son; he has been employed a little at my business, but not much- he lodged in my house; I missed a pair of trousers on the 21st of July, from the room he and his brother slept in - these are them.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I did not steal them - he lent them me to wear; he murdered my mother; when I came out of the House of Correction, I wanted a little money to go to a place, and he told me to go and steal. Witness. No, I never did - I never lent him the trousers; he might have taken them unknown to me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-276-person2284">
                  JAMES 
                  LEVICK
               <interp inst="t18320906-276-person2284" type="surname" value="LEVICK"></interp>
